column51: The study includes isotope values of modern and prehistoric plants. The letters after the numbers indicate the treatment received by the plant. Several types of treatments were performed: b, boiling; c, roasting over charcoal; d, anaerobic carbonization; e, aerobic carbonization; f, ashing; g. removal of carbonates and fulvic and humie acids; h, removal of exchangeable ammonium: I. removal of organics and inorpanics bound by silicates; and j, incubation in a soil microbial bath.
column53: DeNiro, M. J., & Hastorf, C. A. (1985). Alteration of 15N/14N and 13C/12C Ratios of Plant Matter During the Initial Stages of Dagenesis: Studies Utilizing Archaeological Specimens from Peru. Geochimica et Cosmochimica Acta, 49(1), 97–115.
